ODM leader Raila Odinga on Saturday took the Azimio la Umoja campaigns to Machakos County to popularize his presidential bid ahead of the August 9 polls. The Opposition chief was accompanied by a bevy of elected leaders including all three Ukambani Governors Kivutha Kibwana (Makueni), Charity Ngilu (Kitui), and Alfred Mutua of Machakos county. Others were Mombasa Governor Hassan Joho, Narok Senator Ledama ole Kina, Suna East MP Junet Mohamed and his Kieni counterpart Kanini Kega. Raila addressed several stopover rallies in Mlolongo, Athi River and Machakos town where his convoy was received by a mammoth crowd of jubilant supporters.